data.title: TECH / Ms. White, M.A.P.S Teacher
data.text:
Greetings,

My name is Nivea White. I am Seagoville High School P-Tech's M.A.P.S. teacher for the incoming 9th-grade students. I am a proud graduate of Dallas Independent School District at Hillcrest High School. I have a bachelor's degree in Mass Communication with an Emphasis on Public Relations from the University of Arkansas at Pine Bluff and a master's degree in Educational Leadership with an emphasis in STEM from the University of North Texas at Dallas. This is my fourteenth year of teaching and my ninth year at Seagoville High School. During my tenure in education, I have taught English, AP English, Campus Instructional Coach and now M.A.P.S. I've had the privilege of being Teacher of the Year at Seagoville High School in 2014.
